snippet.title: Evolution of Counter Strike Games 1999-2020
snippet.description:
Evolution  of Counter Strike Games from 1999 to 2020

List 

Counter-Strike Half-Life Mod 1999
Counter-Strike 2000 
Counter-Strike Neo 2003
Counter-Strike Condition Zero 2004 
Counter-Strike Source 2004  
Counter-Strike Condition Zero: Deleted Scenes 2004 
Counter-Strike Online 2008  
Counter-Strike 2D 2009   
Counter-Strike: Global Offensive 2012  
Counter-Strike Online 2 2013 
Counter-Strike Nexon: Zombies 2014  
Counter-Strike Global Offensive Danger Zone 2019 
Counter-Strike Global Offensive 2020

Special thanks to World of Longplays: 
https://longplays.org
https://www.youtube.com/recordedamigagames

Nixian Channel Description:

We’re lifelong video game enthusiasts with a passion for showing the world how our favorite hobby has grown with us, from individual series to industry-wide retrospectives.

We put significant time and creative effort into each one of our videos, including research, digging into archives, recording voiceovers, and editing. Every video takes as many as 10 hours to produce, because we strive to give our fans consistent, high-quality content.

Our popular “Evolution of...” series goes far beyond simply presenting gameplay footage. We take the time to show how a video game property — its gameplay, character designs, graphics, sound direction, etc. — have evolved over time. We include unique voiceover work on each video to enhance the viewing experience.

People have been playing video games for decades. In that time, we’ve gone from moving a white line up and down to block a moving pixel, to participating in full-fledged, painstakingly rendered real-time battles with people all over the world. We help older gamers look back on how these experiences have changed throughout their lives, and new gamers to understand the broader context of the series they’re playing for the first time today.
The video game medium never stops growing, and we’ll never stop chronicling its evolution.
Recording, Editing, and voice over were made by me.

snippet.title: Firearms Expert Reacts To Counter-Strike Franchise's Guns
snippet.description:
Jonathan Ferguson, a weapons expert and Keeper of Firearms & Artillery at the Royal Armouries, breaks down the insane weaponry of the Counter-Strike franchise, including the iconic AK47 automatic rifle, the FNP90 submachine gun, and the many versions of the AR-15/M4 rifle.

In the latest video in the Firearm Expert Reacts series, Jonathan Ferguson--a weapons expert and Keeper of Firearms & Artillery at the Royal Armouries--breaks down the guns of the Counter-Strike franchise, and compares them to their real-life counterparts.

If you're interested in seeing more of Jonathan's work, you can check out more from the Royal Armouries right here. - https://www.youtube.com/user/RoyalArmouries

If you would like to support the Royal Armouries, you can make a charitable donation to the museum here. - https://royalarmouries.org/support-us/donations/

And if you would like to become a member of the Royal Armouries, you can get a membership here. - https://royalarmouries.org/support-us/membership/

Facebook tag: gamingrevenant

---------------------------------------------------------------

* Video segments *

First round: 00:05
Final round (Win): 03:44

---------------------------------------------------------------

* Map Info *

Creator(s) of the map: Daniel

A jurassicpark-themed map, as can be told from the spawns since you walk through the iconic gates. Lots of dinosaurs, parkour, vehicles... you name it! This is a really long map for CS1.6 ZE standards, so it's a nice switch off the other shorter maps, and truly one of the best longer maps out there! At the end, the helicopter will stop at two towers, so even if you're defending late, you still have a chance for survival.

---------------------------------------------------------------

GAMEPLAY MODE: Zombie Escape

Zombie Escape is a Source Mod that runs in CS, CS:S and CS:GO. The goal is to escape as a team (CT's) from the infected (T) that get randomly chosen each round. During the escaping attempt, random and fixed events may happen that reward special items to aid in pushing back the zombies. If the team succeeds in surviving, they win and the zombies are slayed.

If the opposite is true, all humans will become infected and all hope is lost! Make sure to bring good teamwork to the table as you'll need it to overcome some of the harder challenges such as boss battles and giant zombie hordes.

---------------------------------------------------------------

snippet.title: Evolution of Counter Strike 1999-2018
snippet.description:
Evolution of Counter Strike from 1999 to 2018

List 

Counter Strike Half-Life Mod 1999
Counter Strike 1.0 (2000)
Counter-Strike 1.3 (2001)      
Counter-Strike 1.5 (2002)  
Counter-Strike 1.6 (2003) 
Counter-Strike: Condition Zero 2004 
Counter-Strike: Source 2004  
Counter-Strike: Global Offensive 2012-2018

Special thanks to World of Longplays: 
https://longplays.org
https://www.youtube.com/recordedamigagames

Song https://youtu.be/Z7aqfIwrvnE

Cussan Channel Description:

We’re lifelong video game enthusiasts with a passion for showing the world how our favorite hobby has grown with us, from individual series to industry-wide retrospectives.

We put significant time and creative effort into each one of our videos, including research, digging into archives, recording voiceovers, and editing. Every video takes as many as 10 hours to produce, because we strive to give our fans consistent, high-quality content.

Our popular “Evolution of...” series goes far beyond simply presenting gameplay footage. We take the time to show how a video game property — its gameplay, character designs, graphics, sound direction, etc. — have evolved over time. We include unique voiceover work on each video to enhance the viewing experience.

People have been playing video games for decades. In that time, we’ve gone from moving a white line up and down to block a moving pixel, to participating in full-fledged, painstakingly rendered real-time battles with people all over the world. We help older gamers look back on how these experiences have changed throughout their lives, and new gamers to understand the broader context of the series they’re playing for the first time today.

The video game medium never stops growing, and we’ll never stop chronicling its evolution.

Recording, Editing, and voice over were made by me.

snippet.title: The Story of CS:GO: The Game That Never Dies
snippet.description:
Counter-Strike: Global Offensive isn’t just a game, it’s a way of life. A culture. A community. One of the oldest institutions in all of esports.

It doesn’t matter whether you’re flicking your AWP, flipping your knife, winning a Major or rushing B after a few beers. You’re engaging in some of the most esteemed and elemental practices in esports.

And whatever happens, whatever the future holds for the beautiful, ballistic thing that is Counter-Strike, it isn’t going anywhere.

Edited By: Sebastien Martin-Schultz (@Seb_dot)

First round: 00:05
Second round: 02:37

---------------------------------------------------------------

* Map Info *

Creator(s) of the map: /

Realm is a pretty decent map, with a nice theme that made me think of ze_egypt. It is one of the rare maps that uses rotating brushes as a kind of obstacle. I really liked it overall and it is pretty tense at the end. It's only drawback is that the nuketrigger comes in very early, often giving zombies little chance at winning or at least striking back properly.

Overall a recommendation!

---------------------------------------------------------------

GAMEPLAY MODE: Zombie Escape

Zombie Escape is a Source Mod that runs in CS, CS:S and CS:GO. The goal is to escape as a team (CT's) from the infected (T) that get randomly chosen each round. During the escaping attempt, random and fixed events may happen that reward special items to aid in pushing back the zombies. If the team succeeds in surviving, they win and the zombies are slayed.

If the opposite is true, all humans will become infected and all hope is lost! Make sure to bring good teamwork to the table as you'll need it to overcome some of the harder challenges such as boss battles and giant zombie hordes.

---------------------------------------------------------------

snippet.title: People Still Play Counter-Strike 1.6 !?
snippet.description:
Today we revisit a classic, join me on this nostalgic journey as we rediscover the magic of Counter-Strike 1.6, truly a remarkable game for its time.  Are people still playing it?  What has become of the 1.6 community?  Sorry for the clickbait, the REAL title is in the Description: "Lost Youth, The Remnants of Counter-Strike".  What made gaming in the late 90s and early 2000s so great?  Community.
